James asked about the basis for his practice of placing punctuation outside of double-quotes when quoting specific terms. The AI explained that this practice is related to the difference between American and British style punctuation. While American style requires placing all punctuation inside the quotation marks, British style suggests placing punctuation inside only if it is part of the original quote. The AI pointed out that James' practice is in line with the British style, which prioritizes logical clarity and accuracy. It also mentioned that different style guides endorse different styles, with American guides favoring the American style. It advised James to be consistent in his usage or follow the preferred style guide of his editor, publisher, or organization.
